President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Arkansas and has ordered federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. This declaration comes in response to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred in the state starting on October 29, 2009. Federal funding will be available to assist with emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The designated counties eligible for assistance include Boone, Bradley, Calhoun, Carroll, Cleburne, Cleveland, Columbia, Conway, Cross, Dallas, Franklin, Fulton, Grant, Izard, Jackson, Johnson, Lafayette, Lawrence, Lincoln, Logan, Marion, Monroe, Nevada, Newton, Ouachita, Poinsett, Prairie, Pulaski, Randolph, Saint Francis, Scott, Sharp, Stone, Union, Van Buren, White, and Woodruff. W. Michael Moore has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-4600.